00:16:57,470 --> 00:16:58,470
I didn't answer him.

289
00:16:58,580 --> 00:17:00,020
I was afraid of hurting his pride.

290
00:17:00,640 --> 00:17:03,000
Because, honestly, I had
never experienced that way.

291
00:17:03,830 --> 00:17:04,990
But

292
00:17:05,390 --> 00:17:06,340
now...

293
00:17:07,630 --> 00:17:08,740
I finally understand it.

294
00:17:09,100 --> 00:17:09,950
So,

295
00:17:09,960 --> 00:17:12,020
now you've gone
from a highly capable top student

296
00:17:12,100 --> 00:17:13,300
to a less capable top student,

297
00:17:13,670 --> 00:17:15,230
and you can't accept it?

298
00:17:17,390 --> 00:17:18,260
Not exactly.

299
00:17:23,230 --> 00:17:24,500
It's not that I can't accept

300
00:17:24,540 --> 00:17:25,780
being less capable than others.

301
00:17:27,500 --> 00:17:28,630
It's just that...

302
00:17:31,500 --> 00:17:32,710
I feel like I could be better.

303
00:17:37,910 --> 00:17:38,820
You know,

304
00:17:39,470 --> 00:17:40,580
sculptures

305
00:17:40,630 --> 00:17:41,670
like Venus

306
00:17:41,910 --> 00:17:43,780
weren't unique in ancient Greece.

307
00:17:45,340 --> 00:17:46,190
But only this one

308
00:17:46,230 --> 00:17:47,300
that lost its arms

309
00:17:47,420 --> 00:17:48,910
became an unsurpassable masterpiece

310
00:17:48,950 --> 00:17:50,190
in art history.

311
00:17:52,040 --> 00:17:53,340
Because of its imperfections

312
00:17:54,190 --> 00:17:54,990
that spark

313
00:17:54,990 --> 00:17:56,260
people's imagination even more?

314
00:17:56,870 --> 00:17:57,670
Maybe.

315
00:17:58,630 --> 00:17:59,540
But,

316
00:17:59,670 --> 00:18:01,390
I prefer another interpretation.

317
00:18:04,950 --> 00:18:06,020
There is no such thing

318
00:18:06,760 --> 00:18:07,870
as perfection in this world.

319
00:18:08,910 --> 00:18:10,100
To be human

320
00:18:10,780 --> 00:18:11,740
is to be flawed.

321
00:18:12,950 --> 00:18:13,950
It's not just you.

322
00:18:14,390 --> 00:18:15,340
Everyone is the same.

323
00:18:16,470 --> 00:18:17,150
Oh, by the way,

324
00:18:17,380 --> 00:18:18,780
I have something to tell you.

325
00:18:19,580 --> 00:18:21,390
I'm transferring
to the Literature department.

326
00:18:23,230 --> 00:18:24,540
Although I don't know

327
00:18:24,540 --> 00:18:25,870
whether the path of literature

328
00:18:25,870 --> 00:18:27,260
will be bright in the future,

329
00:18:27,950 --> 00:18:28,950
I believe

330
00:18:29,540 --> 00:18:31,260
that as long as I'm firm in my choice,

331
00:18:33,020 --> 00:18:34,780
no matter what
difficulties I encounter,

332
00:18:36,190 --> 00:18:37,230
nothing will stop me

333
00:18:37,230 --> 00:18:38,060
from moving forward.

334
00:18:42,630 --> 00:18:43,740
So, Song Cong,

335
00:18:45,430 --> 00:18:46,950
stop overthinking.

336
00:18:47,580 --> 00:18:48,390
Close your eyes

337
00:18:48,460 --> 00:18:49,620
and keep moving forward,

338
00:18:50,910 --> 00:18:52,020
you will make it through.

339
00:19:00,540 --> 00:19:01,100
Alright.

340
00:19:23,380 --> 00:19:23,910
(Piggy Jing)

341
00:19:23,910 --> 00:19:25,280
